# Public display typography (viewport height)

Text on the **venue / TV display** (`apps/display/**`) must stay legible from across a room.

## Two scopes — do not mix them

| Scope | When | Primary | Secondary |
|-------|------|---------|-----------|
| **Full viewport** | Page headers, question strip, pairing screen, countdowns | **~10vh** | **≥ 5vh** |
| **`@container` cell** | Mosaic tile, table card, seat ring inside a tile | **~10cqh** (or `10cqw`) | **≥ 5cqh** |

**Never apply `vh` floors inside small `@container` cells.** `max(5vh, 5cqh)` forces viewport-sized type into a mosaic tile and breaks the 20-table floor.

Use `display-text-primary` / `display-text-secondary` for viewport copy; use `display-text-primary-cq`, `display-text-secondary-cq`, etc. for container copy.

## Full-viewport implementation

- Prefer **`vh`** over fixed `px`, `rem`, or Tailwind `text-xs` / `text-sm`.
- Use **`clamp(5vh, 10vh, 12vh)`** for primary; **`clamp(5vh, 5vh, 7vh)`** for secondary.

## @container implementation

- Prefer **`cqh` / `cqw`** with **`clamp(5cqh, 10cqh, …)`** — same *percent-of-box* intent as vh, but relative to the cell.
- Parent must have **`@container`** (or `@container/size`).

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — vh floor inside a mosaic tile
<span className="display-text-primary-cq">$5,000</span>
// where CSS is max(5vh, 10cqh) → always 5vh, overflows tile

// ✅ GOOD — container-relative only
// CSS: font-size: clamp(5cqh, 10cqh, 14cqh);
```

## Checklist before merging display UI changes

- [ ] Viewport headlines/questions use **`display-text-primary`** / **`secondary`** (vh).
- [ ] Mosaic tiles, felts, and cards use **`*-cq` / `*-cqw`** tokens — **no `vh` in those utilities**.
- [ ] No display copy uses Tailwind `text-xs`, `text-sm`, or px/rem sizes on venue screens.
